<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-01-09T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-01-09T16:00:00-05:00" n="117" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d117">
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Page</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-01-09T16:00:00-05:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">January 9, 1918, 4 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>6202. Your January 1, 2 p.m., No. 8116. The report communicated by
                                Foreign Office December 31 to effect that Japanese group had decided
                                to defer the making of proposed advance is proved incorrect.
                                American Legation at Peking January 7 informs Department that loan
                                was signed January 6.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>